    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_11_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_11",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) represents a concours-level preservation of the S54-powered platform. The 3.2L high-compression inline-six features individual throttle bodies and a 7,900 RPM redline, paired with a tactile Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a variable M differential lock. Mechanically flawless, this example has received comprehensive preventative maintenance including a dual-VANOS overhaul with Beisan components, rod bearing replacement, and a reinforced rear subframe. The suspension geometry is dialed in with fresh bushings and Bilstein dampers, ensuring the chassis remains as rigid and communicative as the day it left Regensburg. Finished in Carbon Black Metallic with zero orange peel or swirl marks, this is a turn-key masterpiece for the serious driver.",
